From 7ff176831784e5c3d66d5043725328b9b2bed856 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Golle <daniel@makrotopia.org>
Date: Wed, 25 Feb 2026 02:46:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 02/24] meson: allow external tokens without dlvsym (musl)

dlvsym is a glibc extension that some libc implementations (notably
musl) do not provide. The C code already handles this gracefully since
commit 5f2c751d ("Use dlsym() for token load if dlvsym() is not
available"), falling back to dlsym when HAVE_DLVSYM is not set.

However, the meson build had an assert requiring HAVE_DLVSYM for
external-tokens, making it impossible to build with external token
support on musl.

Remove the assert and always set HAVE_DLVSYM via conf.set10() so that
config.h gets the correct value, matching the autotools behaviour.
---
 meson.build | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -201,14 +201,14 @@ if not cc.has_function('dlsym',
         error('dlsym not found')
     endif
 endif
-if cc.has_function('dlvsym',
+have_dlvsym = cc.has_function('dlvsym',
         dependencies: dl)
-    conf.set10('HAVE_DLVSYM', true)
+conf.set10('HAVE_DLVSYM', have_dlvsym)
+if not have_dlvsym
+    warning('dlvsym not found, external token plugins will use dlsym as fallback.')
 endif
 
 if get_option('external-tokens')
-    assert(conf.has('HAVE_DLVSYM') and conf.get('HAVE_DLVSYM') == 1,
-        'dl library has no dlvsym function')
     conf.set10('USE_EXTERNAL_TOKENS', true,
         description: 'Use external tokens')
 endif
